cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MED, cs.AI, cs.IR 

The paper deals with training and evaluating deep convolutional neural networks on a large dataset of chest x-ray images to recognize multiple thorax diseases. This task involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques, which are covered under the cs.CV and cs.LG sub-categories. The dataset used in the paper is related to medical imaging, which falls under the cs.MED sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel architecture for processing both frontal and lateral CXR images, which involves AI techniques and could be classified under the cs.AI sub-category. Finally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for extracting radiology reports from the dataset.
